arch:property.oc:show_val: Phase VI: Late Nabataean pre CE 106 minor collapses and repairs. Probable early collapse of the Baroque Room and damage occurs in both the Anteroom and Shrine Room. The tabun in Room A is used to store CE 1st c. Nabataean fine wares. East 'Cistern" used as a dump. Bath Complex built.
Part of the north architectural boundary of the trench.
Construction of the Well Room and the canalization system.
Part of the north architectural boundary of the Trench.
The northwest architectural niche was originally intended to be a space used for the drawing of water and was excavated to floor level. The wall is 12 courses in height and two rows in thickness.
